The paper discusses random graph models and their generation algorithms, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. The focus on scalable generators suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category, as it deals with large-scale network data and their analysis. The discussion of algorithmic primitives and models of computation suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) as likely categories. The mention of different domains and their specific models suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category. Finally, the use of machine learning techniques for network analysis suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as a possible category.
